<concept id="_6_3_conceptual_design">
    <title>6.3 Conceptual Design</title>
    <shortdesc>This is the phase where you need to focus on potential costs, revenues, and
        profitability. </shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <fig id="fig_myy_y5y_pbc">
            <title>Third step - Conceptual Design</title>
            <image
                href="../image/PNG/6%20Stages%20of%20Product%20Development/4_6%20Stages%20of%20Product%20Development.png.png"
                scale="60" id="image_nyy_y5y_pbc">
                <alt>Third stepis conceptual design</alt>
            </image>
        </fig>
        <p>This is the phase where you need to focus on potential costs, revenues, and
            profitability. </p>
        <p>Here's what to do:</p>
        <ul id="ul_yyb_w5y_pbc">
            <li>
                <p>After the market analysis, revisit your value proposition and ensure it aligns
                    with potential customers' expectations.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Look for ways to add or improve features that your competitors lack or don't
                    execute well.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Develop the final value proposition into a <xref
                        href="8_glossary.dita#feasibility_study">Feasibility Study</xref> for the
                    product. Pay special attention to technical feasibility and implementation
                    risks.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Create a business model that focuses on the billing model, distribution channels,
                    and the main sources of revenue and costs.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </conbody>
</concept>
